threads.title: 820-00164 Everything is present but no post
threads.message: This board was hit in multiple spots by liquid. I included pre-ultrasonic-cleaning pictures. I replace the LCD connector. Board is not posting. All voltages are present the that I can possible think to check. Vcore is good. All U1950 voltages are present and normal compared to a good board. S0 voltages are present. No chime. PRAM does nothing. I'm out of ideas.

threads.title: 820-00164 Everything is present but no post
threads.message:
Pufff, I saw liquid sign on the MOSFETs from CPU power supply :(
If you don't find some corroded resistor/trace, on the board, could be dead CPU...

Try new BIOS, just in case.
Also check all SPi Bus series Termination resistors.
J6100 looks bad too, maybe need to remove it.

threads.title: 820-00164 Everything is present but no post
threads.message: Any USB activity at all? If no, def try new BIOS and U6101 could be one of them seeing you had corrosion there. Also assuming you definitely removed the JTAG
